   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_XXXX_1817_05_08_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">EdgeworthsTown</placeName>
                  <date when="1817-05-08">May 8</date><lb/>
                  1817<lb/>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF1">Brother</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I will not scruple to put you<lb/>
               to the expence of a letter, when I feel that it<lb/>
               will save me some anxiety.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I wrote to you yesterday to beg<lb/>
                  that you would get <title ref="./Workography.xml#Ormon1">Ormond</title> from <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntX1">Hunter</persName> -<lb/>
               - Now I fear, that he might by soft words<lb/>
               and delusive promises, prevail upon you<lb/>
               to leave it with him - _. I therefore beg, that<lb/>
               you will in the first place possess yourself of<lb/>
               the manuscript. and inform me of it, before<lb/>
                  we enter into any <choice>
                  <orig>negociation</orig>
                  <reg>negotation</reg>
               </choice> with him or<lb/>
               any body else - possession being nine points<lb/>
               of the law. - .<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>What keeps your book in the<lb/>
               dark? -. Don't forget my values -.</p>
            <lb/>
            <closer>
               Yours sincerely<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">RLE</persName>
               <lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_XXXX_1817_05_08_page02.jpg"/>
               <note>R L. E<lb/>
                  8 May 1817</note>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
         </div>
      </body>
